A 32-year old cemetery worker Seun Owoyemi has been remanded at the Olokuta Correctional Centre for allegedly raping a female minor. He was said to have committed the offence on January 10 at Igesa Street, Igbara-Oke, headquarters of Ifedore local government. Owoyemi was alleged to have lured his victim with the sum of N100 and had unlawful carnal knowledge of her twice. Police prosecutor, Inspector Niyi Taiwo, informed the court that the offence contravened provisions of the Criminal Code, Cap. 37, Vol. 1 Laws of Ondo State.   Gombe NSCDC boss charges officers on ending insecurity     FG asks Customs to generate N3.019tr in 2022     Kizz Daniel announces 2022 world tour   - Advertisement - He however pleaded not guilty to the charge even as he stated in a statement that the allegation was planned to implicate him by the victim and her grandmother. Presiding Magistrate, O.L. Abu, remanded the defendant to the Correctional Centre and orderd the prosecutor to duplicate the case file and send to the Department of Public Prosecution for legal advice. The case was adjourned to February 28, 2022, for mentioning.